Class Node<CONTENT,CHILD>

  • Object
    • Node<CONTENT,CHILD>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    InvNode, PptNode, RootNode

    public abstract class Node<CONTENT,CHILD>
extends Object
    All nodes must subclass this class. The type parameter CONTENT is (half of) the type of the objects stored in this node: they are Pair<CONTENT,CONTENT>. The type parameter CHILD is the type of the children (and is ignored if there are no children).
